parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or lose motive power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes oil at an abnormal rate
the vehicle stalls or loses motive power
and there may be signs of oil leakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose motive power, resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses motive power
the check engine warning light illuminates
and the vehicle may experience a loss of acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: and the vehicle may experience a loss of acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the service brake hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause the vehicle to catch fire.
symptoms: The ABS warning light is illuminated
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the odometer spikes up to the 20-mile mark
and the vehicle fails to accelerate from a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in receiving parts for the recall repair can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The contact receives notification of the recall
but the part to do the recall repair is not yet available
or the dealer is unable to provide a repair date.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the service brake hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in significant damage or total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire while driving or parked

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can lead to accidents, strand the driver, and cause costly repairs.
symptoms: Burning oil at an extremely fast rate

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden loss of power, hesitation, or stalling can lead to accidents, especially when merging into traffic or crossing intersections.
Differential failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and costly repairs.
Clutch and hydraulic system failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and costly repairs.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
